Variables:
Are like boxes/containers which can hold data for us. We can change the data later on if we
want. We can reuse the same variable as many times as we
want. There are 8 basic/primitive data types.
Four basic data types to store whole numbers.
1)byte 2)short 3)int 4)long
2 basic/primitive data types to store decimal numbers
5)float 6)double
1 basic/primitive data type to store characters
7)char
To store true/false
8)boolean

NonPrimitives: Advanced data types
1)String